SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Mar, 25th , around 4.30 pm I got vaccinated. I went back home. I ate my summer and Took Tyelenol as I was tired and arm was little sore. I slept around 7.30 pm and got up at 7 am. I felt weakness and after I had my break fast , my body pains started. Every muscle ached and every joint ached. I had weakness and lethargy. I took tyelenol extra strength so the pain was subsiding . I had temperature 100.3 since Fri , Mar 25th. When the tyelenol was wearing off the pains used to become horrible. I was not able to move and I was on my bed bed most of the time. On 28th I even tried Ibuprofen as Tyelenol was not helping a lot with pains but Ibuprofen did not work at all. I sent messages to my dr who thought these side effects are expected. On Mon she replied if the side effects did not resolve I can go to Immediate Care. My arm was sore but that soreness was nothing compared to body aches I had. I called off from work on Fri and Sat. My employer wanted return to work clearance. I went to discuss with Immediate care doctor as I had same weakness and tiredness and little walking was making me breathe heavily. As it was almost the end of 4th day after I got my vaccine they tested me for Covid and my results were negative.  I still have to be in quarantine for 7 days from yesterday.  I was tested Covid positive in Mar 2020 around mar 24th. I had same horrible pains but had high temperature like 1049.8 and with tyelenol it was 102.5. I am scared to take the second dose that might trigger same reaction. I suffered a lot like people suffered after 2nd dose. First dose is sensitizing dose but I showed such reaction that means my body recognized the threat and began to fight in first dose then what is the need of second dose that is actually a booster dose. My main concern is I might feel the same way how I felt now. I am still weak and cannot perform my daily activities like cooking and I have 4 kids aged 7- 12 yrs age.
LAB_DATA: Covid test , flu test A and B
OTHER_MEDS: Tyelenol extra strength , Levoxyl 125mcg, Calcium supplements 750 mg, Vit D 400
HISTORY: Thyroidectomy due to papillary carcinoma Chrohn's

SYMPTOM_TEXT: By late afternoon my left arm and armpit felt a little sore.   I went to bed around 8 p.m. and awoke at 11 p.m. ~12 hours after receiving my second vaccination, with chills, arthralgias, myalgias, headache, a slightly stiff neck.  I got up to take some Acetominophen and Ibuprofen.  My hands shook badly and I had trouble opening the bottles and getting out a couple of pills (APAP 500 mg, Ibuprofen 400 mg).  I returned to bed and eventually the symptoms subsided and I fell asleep.  In the morning I had extreme lethargy, felt dizzy after standing a few minutes to the point of pre-syncope as I made it back into bed.  I slept on and off most of the day (Saturday).  By Sunday, I was much improved but still had little energy and took it easy.  My left axilla still felt a little full but I could not detect any lymph nodes.  By Monday, I was pretty much back to normal including my left arm and axilla.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient reports routinely having spells of syncope with injections and still insisted on receiving COVID-19 vaccination. Gave injection into left deltoid. Had patient scoot up to table in immunization room with both legs fully under the table just in case there was an issue. I set the timer for 15 minutes and left him in the immunization room with his girlfriend, who also received a vaccine. A few moments later the girlfriend asked for our help stating he was feeling like he was going to pass out. I went into the IMZ room and checked with him. At the time, he was sweaty with a rapid hearbeat. I instructed him to take some deep breaths and went to get a cold paper towel to apply to his head. When I returned he had passed out, not responsive but still breathing, in his chair and his girlfriend was holding his head in her hand. We gently lowered his head to rest on the table while another associate called 911 per girlfriend's request. He began moaning a few moments later and was able to talk to us. He was very hot and sweaty, light headed and breathing rapidly. We applied a cooling pack to his forhead as he continued to lie his head on the table. He then said he might feel more comfortable lying on the floor. We assisted him to the floor, elevated his feet on a chair and placed his head on a roll of paper towels. At that time the paramedics showed up and said his blood pressure was fine and he was just having some hyperventilation. The paramedics got him back up in the chair and his girlfriend got him some apply juice. After about 30 minutes he was talking fine, shaking had stopped and his breathing a temp went back to normal

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my vaccine on a Tuesday morning, and five days later on Sunday morning I woke up with very swollen checks--my head looked like a pumpkin.  When my girlfriend saw me in the afternoon, she said, "I'm taking you to the emergency room!"  But, I told her that I had no fever and no other symptoms, so we should wait.  The swelling was bad enough that my jaws ached and my cheeks felt like they were going to burst, but if I didn't chew any food, the swelling would subside slightly, and my jaws would stop aching.   I read online that people with botox who get the vaccine can have facial swelling and a 24 hour course of benadryl will knock down the swelling.  I have never had botox injections, but I took some benadryl for two days, which made me feel really tired.  I ate only soup and yogurt, so that I didn't have to chew any food.   I don't know if the benadryl had any effect, but over about 5 days, the swelling subsided, then I could eat again without causing my jaws to swell up.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Sensitivity started within four hours of dose. Autistic sensitivities to maximum. Scrambling of all senses including proprioception to the point of not being able to move from standing  or sitting. By hour seven, all sensory inputs were too overwhelming to do anything but shut down and sleep. 911 was not an option because they don't let you sleep, and ERs are overwhelming already, before maximizing all inputs. 7.5 mg hydrocodone for overwhelming pain and sensitivity, allowed sleep. On waking, sensitivity was lessened, but the pain started, 18 hours after the vaccination. Emotional lability for three days. Average aching of arm and injection site were not above expected levels. "Brain fog" and lack of ability to articulate (another autism symptom) started within that first seven hours, and diminished over next ten days. Not yet gone as of today  Dry mouth; overproduction of thick 'chunky' mucus that wouldn't cough out, treated with guaifenesin, lasted three days. Shortness of breath and cough associated with that mucus also diminished after three days. Not completely gone ten days later.   Excessive thirst, onset two hours after vaccine, lasted two days.   Hyperalert (can't sleep without drugs), hyperactive despite weakness, and hypervigilant (extreme startle reflexes) lasted three days as well. Sleep was achieved with hydrocodone and THC.  All over body pain, feelings of immune mobilization (coming down with) for two days were not above expected levels.   No fainting or other collapse at time of injection, or later.  Knowing that severe over-stimulation is exacerbated in a medical setting, it was decided not to seek medical support for three days of systemic symptoms that would have easily merited hospitalization.
OTHER_MEDS: Potassium Cl 20 mEq/day; THC 3.25 mg/day; Magnesium Cl 1800 mg/day; multi vitamin; garlic extract; turmeric curcumin; flax oil.
PRIOR_VAX: Shingrix 2018, similar neurological overwhelm, but nowhere near as much. Sought medical support, which made all of the symptoms

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I lost my memory on Friday, March 26, at 10 pm. I do not remember what I did Wednesday-Friday, and the information I am providing is what my family and boyfriend have informed me about. I received my second Pfizer dose on Wednesday, March 24, at 11 am on my right arm. At 8 pm, I had a horrible migraine, body ache, and 101 fever. On Thursday, the fever was gone, and I just had a body ache and severe headache. On Friday, the body ache was gone, but the migraine was still present. I drove to my boyfriend's house at 8 pm. At 10 pm I informed my boyfriend that for 5 minutes I forgot where I was and that I forgot his room. He told me that I complained of a pounding headache that felt like it took over my whole head.  My boyfriend said to me that I had body chills and that my head was warm, but my hands were freezing. The last thing I said to him before I lost my memory was that the headache was getting worse.   A minute later, I started panicking because I forgot my birthday and my name. He said that I had brain fog and that I lost my memory. I was in a dream-like state and looked confused. I thought I was ten years old and could not remember certain family members or who I was. I was informed I lost my memory for 12 hours. On Saturday, I woke up and did not recall what happened the previous night. It felt like I woke up from a long sleep. My headache was still present, and my head felt foggy. I have tried to remember those three days, and when I try, the headaches become severe.  I reported this to my doctor, and she informed me that I need to report this since the same thing happened to my mother. She received the first Pfizer vaccine on March 3, at 11 am, and on March 7, she lost her memory. The only difference between my mother and I is that she lost her memory after the first vaccine, and  I lost my memory after the second vaccine.  I lost my memory for 12 hours, and for her, it was 24 hours. We both lost three days, and when we try to remember, we get headaches.
LAB_DATA: I did not get any medical tests since the same thing happened to my mother. When she went to the clinic, they diagnosed her with global transit amnesia. My family kept me home and hoped that I would gain my memory back; if I did not, they would take me to the clinic. I informed my doctor about this when I had my doctor's appointment on Monday, March 29.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: got up about 5:15AM to use the restroom, parents heard a huge crash and we came running - he had collapsed and fainted in the bathroom, against the toilet, (with shelves and glass crashing down him - he grabbed the shelves and had a few cuts and bruises), was unresponsive, no color in his face, could not stand or move, could barely speak - slumped against the toilet.  Parents called 911 and tried to get him to respond, he was listless but opened his eyes - we lifted him and moved him to recliner in living room.  Fire Dept./EMT's arrived within a few minutes, blood pressure was 87/43, glucose was normal.  EMT's determined it was a reaction to the vaccine and asked if he wanted an ambulance or if parents should drive him for further care - he opted for us to drive him (his Mom called the Dr. on staff first - Dr. said it was a reaction to the vaccine and he should not get a 2nd dose).  Patient's Dad took him to Urgent Care - they ran an EKG (normal), and stayed there until his blood pressure showed (although still low)  normal/acceptable again.  I looked at the CDC website for covid anaphylaxis and it appears it was an allergic reaction (cardiovascular), on the site, he had these symptoms:  "Cardiovascular: fainting; hypotension (abnormally low blood pressure); pallor.  ... Symptoms of anaphylaxis often occur within 15-30 minutes of vaccination, though it can sometimes take several hours for symptoms to appear."
LAB_DATA: Done by 911 EMT's - blood pressure, oxygen level, pulse, glucose Done by Urgent Care:  EKG, blood pressure (he was NOT given epinephrine by any medical staff or EMT's)
OTHER_MEDS: No medications. Just a daily multi vitamin & Calcium with Vit. D supplement
ALLERGIES: Allergic to:  Amoxicillin (hives), Zithromax/Zpack (hives), Cefrozil (hives), Omnicef (severe diahreah). Sensitivity to: lactose/milk products (stomach issues), pumpkin seeds/pepitas (severe stomach pains).

I went to see my doctor and he diagnosed me with shingles specifically Ramsay-Hunt Syndrome with Bells Palsy. As a result of my condition I had to take four weeks of medical leave. I was very fatigued that I was stuck in bed for two weeks.  I felt a little better after four weeks my energy level was still very low. I still have residual dizziness. I am working three quarters of my work schedule after eleven weeks. I still have a lot of the paralysis and I can't blink my eye I have to tape it shut. I have trouble eating and My right ear swelling is reduced but it is still itchy. My doctor prescribed Acyclovir for one week and now I am taking Famciclovir. I do not have as much pain as I did.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: PT reported feeling normal immediately after vaccine was administered. According to PT, they began feeling extremely lightheaded approximately 5 minutes post-injection. Approximately 8 minutes post-injection, I observed the patient rise from her seat and begin to stumble towards me. The patient was exceptionally pale, and reported to me that she was feeling light headed. I promptly directed the patient to sit down, but before she was able to reach a chair, she collapsed entirely. She fully regained consciousness within a few seconds and was alert to presence, place, and time. PT was able to seat herself at this point.  Her blood pressure registered 82/51 mmHg immediately after the episode. PT was visually slowed and confused, but was otherwise fully present. PT was given water and allowed to recover in a seated position.  Blood pressure registered at 117/71 mmHg 15 minutes later, and PT reported feeling much better. PT was visually much more alert and cognitively present. After 15 minutes of no change in condition, patient was allowed to leave facility with the accompaniment of her mother. No epinephrine or antihistamines were administered.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: March 19 Herpes simplex outbreak left mos pubis, mild symptoms; diminished by March 21.  Followed by mild  pre-outbreak nerve sensitivity around the waist. Pulses of shooting pain extending from the jaw to ear and temple (right side) kept me awake for most of the night.  The pain subsided somewhat over subsequent days.  Having had shingles at age 24 I suspected that this was the cause, but also  (despite no indication that this was related to a sinus infection) I proceeded with daily salt and betadyne solution sinus rinses just to be cautious. About 48 hrs after my shot I started to experience symptoms (headache, agitation, chest tightness) that I wrote off for a few days. I called and my cardiologist's office told me to go to urgent care or the ER to get checked out.  I went to urgent care and was sent on to the ER after and ekg and a physical just to be safe.  I was sent home from the ER after an ekg, blood draw, and chest x-ray and told to follow up with my doctor.  I called my cardiologist and he adjusted my meds saying that he has seen this reaction happen before and it ought to resolve itself with time.  The meds adjustment fixed the headaches, agitation, and chest tightness, but my blood pressure is like a roller coaster still and it's 12 days out from my vaccination.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I felt some very mild achiness around 9 am the morning following the injection.  I felt I was moving a bit more slowly also. (I use a walker due to impaired mobility/MS).  No fever but I took Tylenol at that point for the body aches.  I spent the morning in bed to rest but got up around 10 am to shower.  By about 11 am I was really exhausted and got back in bed, still feeling mild achiness.  I got up about an hour later to eat, still feeling wiped out but the body aches were gone.  After eating I sat in a chair and hardly moved until about 5 pm.  I could walk to the restroom but it was a struggle and I had my husband with me to make sure I was ok.  My fine motor control of my hands was severely impaired... couldn't type on the computer or do buttons for example (this happens when my MS flares up).  I took some Ibuprofen around 1 pm and continued to alternate Tylenol and Ibuprofen until about 11 pm.  Around 5 pm I noticed my fingers were working better and I gradually felt better and was able to walk much more easily by 6 pm.  Felt almost back to normal by 9 pm, just a mild lack of energy.  I noticed very mild body aches before bed around 11 when I took my last meds.  I did have a temp of 99 degrees around noon but later it was fine.  Similar fatigue type reaction after I had both the flu and pneumonia vaccines in Sept. 2020,   No fever or body aches.  But couldn't walk for several hours.  Needed wheelchair.
OTHER_MEDS: Synthroid, Lisinopril, Flomax, oral baclofen, baclofen continuous infusion through pump, Ocrevus infusions 2 times per year (last one in early December 2020), vitamin D, multi-vitamin, Viviscal vitamin supplements, vitamin B 12
HISTORY: I have Multiple sclerosis, HTN (well controlled) and hypothyroidism (well controlled), Raynauds, mitral valve prolapse

Her therapist could tell that her whole system was in "overdrive" which was vastly different than her previous session a week ago.  The tremors were so bad that my daughter wanted her wheel chair again.    I took a video of her tremors after her therapy session. Her therapist told us to contact her DO, Dr. about it.  I did.  She was able to crash around 10pm on Monday.  On Tuesday, when she woke up around 2:30pm, she still had the tremors but they weren't as severe. Patient had flu-like symptoms while deployed at start of pandemic (approx. Jan/Feb 2020), but testing was unavailable. His symptoms (URI-like) completely resolved. He received Moderna dose 1 on 02 Feb 2021 without incident, and Moderna dose 2 on 02 Mar 2021. Approximately one week later, he developed mild, dull, diffuse chest pain and shortness of breath which has persisted since.   He was seen in clinic for chest pain and dyspnea on 15 Mar 2021. Patient noted his chest hurt ?all over? especially with deep or with normal inspiration. Reclining, laying down, and sleeping on his right side increased his pain (he did not trial sleeping on his left). Leaning forward decreased pain. He endorsed feeling short of breath, and stated he felt light headed twice while going up stairs, without passing out. He denied recent illnesses and other symptoms. He is a very physically fit Active Duty Marine, who has continued running despite his symptoms. During this encounter and later f/u encounter, he expressed he did not believe running made his symptoms significantly worse.  Vital signs were within normal range and he did not appear in distress. Cardiac and lung exam were normal, and no friction rub or murmur was appreciated. EKG showed sinus bradycardia, with HR consistent with his known, athletic-type normal variant heart rate. No other abnormalities were detected. Due to limited ancillary services within clinic, he was sent to USNHO ED for evaluation. There, he had basic labs (including Trop I) drawn, which were normal. EKG and portable chest xray were also unremarkable, and he was discharged with Motrin 800mg PO TID.  He was seen in clinic again 29 Mar 2021 for continued, unchanged symptoms, and reported he had been taking his Motrin only in the mornings and afternoons. Vital signs were unchanged (normal limits). Exam, including heart and lung, were normal. EKG again demonstrated sinus bradycardia, consistent with his normal resting heart rate. He was started on empiric therapy for pericarditis. He was released from clinic and will follow up in several weeks.

With O2 and rest, my O2 Sat improved and extra O2 was stopped.  Then again my O2 steadily dropped over a period of a week, I coughed more (always have come cough), SOB. On March 7th, getting ready for bed, I became severely SOB, O2 Sat now 82, I called 911.  Was alert, oriented when Paramedics arrived, but needed 100% O2 and transported to Hospital, SOB was severe, gasping/drowning, loss of awareness, apparently resp. arrested, was intubated.  STAT CT with Contrast, and Echocardiogram, R/O PE, Lung collapse, etc.  (No PE/or collapse). MY supposition is that I had a slow moving allergic response to Moderna Vaccine (I am a former healthcare worker of 20 years) and currently work in healthcare medical devices in Ultrasound.  I closely watch vaccine development and read research articles on Sarcoidosis, vaccines and COVID. I participated and continue with a Sarcoidosis Study). I think I experienced cytokine storm with my ultrasensitive immune system. I use oral steroid (QVAR 40mics inhaled daily) which I doubled after taking the vaccine for a few weeks. I have had a MMR vaccine last June 2020 and Quadvalent Flu vaccine last August 2020.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around 10pm on 3/26, I got a slight headache, but I am not sure if it was due to screen time or a vaccine side effect. Per the clinician that administered the shot, I took 2 tabs of Tylenol (one normal adult dose) with water and went to bed. At 1 am on 3/27, I woke up incredibly sore all over but especially in my joints. I was shivering badly and woke up in a tightly curled fetal position. I was unable to lie still or warm up. I eventually went back to sleep and woke up at 5 am, this time with extreme nausea and threw up everything I had eaten the day before. This went on for a couple of minutes. I was still shivering constantly and sore and achy everywhere. Especially in my knees, shoulders, and lower back. At 6 am, I was still awake and while I still had chills, my face felt hot and I took my temperature twice. First getting 100.74 then 100.86. Slept deeply for the rest of the night. At noon on 3/27 I woke up with no nausea,  body aches but only in my joints but with general soreness everywhere (like after a good workout) and a temp still in the 100.7 degree range. I took 2 Tylenol tabs at 2pm. At 4pm, I only had slight body aches, a headache, and a slight brain fog left and my temp was at 98.7, so no more fever. No further problems showed  up and when I woke up at 9 am on 3/28, I felt absolutely fine other than soreness at the injection site and a little chest tightness which last for about 2 days, through 3/30.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: facial swelling, itching, redness right forarm, tingling of lips and face; tongue swelling Narrative:  This is a 54-year-old female with history of significant for sleep apnea, chronic obstructive lung disease, fibromyalgia, and previous allergies to 3 medications, milk and shellfish. The patient received her first dose of Moderna Covid-19 vaccine on 2/26/21. The patient apparently reported itching within 10 minutes and within 20 minutes she developed mild lips and tongue swelling. No breathing difficulty noted. The patient reported taking Benadryl liquid with relief of her symptoms. No Epi Pen was administered. On 3/3/21, the patient was seen by the Immunologist for evaluation as the patient requested to receive her second dose despite potential risk for another allergic reaction. The immunologist recommended to patient's primary care provider to premedicate the patient 1 hour prior to 2nd dose of Moderna with specific instructions for the vaccine to be administered at the Emergency Department. Another option was for the patient not to get the second dose of Moderna and wait for a different vaccine. The patient informed her primary care provider that she wants the 2nd dose administered. On 3/26/21, the patient premedicated herself as instructed from home with fexofenadine 180mg, diphenhydramine 50mg, famotidine 40mg, and prednisone 20mg prior to her 2nd dose of the vaccine. Patient received her second dose of Moderna Covid-19 vaccine around 3:09 pm at the Emergency Department (ED) area. After 15 minutes, the patient had facial swelling and was immediately given Epi Pen in left thigh. Patient was checked in to the ED. Thirty minutes later, the patient experienced itching and redness in her right forearm, headaches, tingling of her lips and face, then found her tongue swelling with difficulty opening her mouth. The patient received her 2nd dose of the Epi Pen in addition to diphenhydramine IV and IV methylprednisolone (steroid). She was later transferred to MICU for further monitoring due to potential airway compromise. The patient was admitted to MICU on 3/26/21. Covid-19 negative. She was transferred to acute care ward on 3/27/21 for additional monitoring of her angioedema. As of 3/29/21, the patient is in a stable condition. Per hospitalist, patient's facial swelling has gradually improved and remains on iv steroid treatment. If the patient is able to tolerate oral steroid and her symptoms continues to improve, the patient will be discharged if patient remains stable.

LAB_DATA: See attached bx result. Thigh, left anterior proximal- NOTE: Multiple deeper level of this biopsy specimen are cut and examined. The histologic features seen in this biopsy specimen are those of a mixed inflammatory reaction in the dermis and extending into the subcutis. This infiltrate is comprised of lymphocytes, histocytes and neutrophils. Focally, eosinophils were also seen. Vascular ectasia and dermal edema were noted. Findings present in this biopsy specimen could represent those of a vaccination site reaction. A hypersensitivity reaction or bite reaction could be included in the histologic differential. GMS stains were performed and were negative for fungal organisms. The specimen is submitted entirely in the single cassette. Due to shrinkage, measurements may be different than those at the time of procedure. Speicmen Size: .4 cm long X .4 cm wide X .3 cm deep.

I am writing in regards to the online form. I attempted to file one online and after filling it out  on the website something  happened that caused me to lose the entire form. I believe that my wife of 34 years passed away on Saturday March 13 2021 from a reaction to the Moderna vaccine 1st dose (010A21A), she was vaccinated on Friday Feb 26 2021 and started showing signs of a reaction on Sunday Feb 28 2021. My wife was having a fever, chills and a headache all of the signs that we were told could happen as her body was building immunity, and how it is considered a good sign. My wife was not a person who complained about pain or discomfort. My wife had worked at the same place since 1989 and had called in "sick" maybe 5 or 6 times including this issue, so she thought something wasn't right. I am not saying that the vaccine "caused any new medical issues" but I do believe that something in it may have interacted with a previously unknown issue. Unfortunately someone is not allowed to just believe something is wrong and has to follow procedure with regards to the Insurance companies and the type of care you receive and how to get it. After a couple of days of the symptoms, late Wednesday night March 3 2021 she called a 24 Nurse hotline sponsored by our Insurance and was told to take Tylenol because she was probably having a reaction and was building immunity and to call her Dr. in the morning and she did call Thursday March 4 2021 and was basically told the same thing to take Tylenol as she was probably just having a reaction and building immunity. Saturday March 6 2021 she was wondering if she actually did have COVID and went to an Urgent Care and had the 15 minute  test and also the 24 hour test the results came Saturday for the 15 test and Sunday for the 24 hour test both were negative. Monday morning she called her Dr and he said that maybe she had Pneumonia and ordered an antibiotic and ordered a chest X-ray. I picked up the prescription and the order. Tuesday March 8 2021 my wife had the chest X-ray and Wednesday she received the results and that was negative. My wife asked to speak to the Dr. and he was supposed to call her when he could. Thursday March 9 2021 my wife went to work and they sent her home which shows how she was. Her Dr called and said to go to the ER I dropped her at the ER and went home because her Mother lives with us and has dementia and and other medical concerns and cannot be alone for long periods. We had agreed to let her live with us because between the two of us we could manage her care, me during the day and my wife after work. Now it is me alone and my wife was "our" only source of income and insurance besides being my "everything" 34 years wasn't long enough and I am sorry that this is not the right place fo that but this is personally very hard on me. My wife texted me and said that they told her she had an infection and they were going to admit her. I visited her Thursday night and she was still having the fever, chills and headaches. I went home and later she texted me after I went to bed said she was hot and asked if we could we talk in the morning and what I didn't know was after I left someone came in and told her that her Dr. thought she might have a heart problem. My wife never told me so as not to worry but that was what she wanted to talk about which I found out Friday. Friday March 10 2021 1 received a phone call that my wife had complained of chest pains and they were taking her to the Heart Catheterization Lab and asked if I wanted to be there and I said that I couldn't because her mother was not awake and hadn't been fed or had any of her medication yet. After taking care of everything I called the Hospital and they said she was already in for the procedure. I received a phone call from the Dr who performed the procedure and he said she had a 100% blockage on one artery and a thickened wall of her heart that was probably hereditary and also a leaky valve but they were going look at that Monday March 15 2021 I called to speak to my wife and was told that she had to lie flat until 10:30 am because of what was done. She called me and said that she felt like she had been run over but was okay, while we were talking my wife told me what the Dr had said about maybe her having a heart problem. My wife said she had to go because someone came in to do something and she would call me later. I received a call from the nurse who said my wife had been light-headed and that her blood pressure was low and her heart rate was too high and they were going to put an IV in her neck to better control the drugs to regulate both of them. They wanted the heart rate lower and her blood pressure higher. I visited her later Friday night and she looked good all things considered we talked and I had to go home to care for her mother. Saturday March 13 20211 called to speak to her and she didn't answer so I called to speak to the nurse but was told she would call me back, I waited for about an hour and went to the Hospital. When I saw my wife she seemed in distress and had an oxygen mask on and was not

The patient received the first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 031M20A) intramuscularly in the left arm on 14 Feb 2021.   On 13 Mar 2021, prior to the onset of the event, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 026A21A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 18 Feb 2021 four days after the first dose of vaccination, patient began to bleed as if their menstrual cycle began. Patient reported that she was at a menopausal phase in life to typically do not bleed not or if they do there was a light pink blood excreted, the last time this had occurred was in November. Patient had a bleeding that was very heavy and contained large blood clots. The event heavy bleeding/ post menopausal bleeding was a medically significant event.  Patient stated that this bleeding lasted 7 consecutive days until 25 Feb 2021. The bleeding then stopped 26 Feb 2021 for 2 days, and then heavy bleeding episode came back again on 28 Feb 2021 for 2 days lasting until 02 March 2021.  On 03 March 2021, patient reported that she had a fever of 102F which lasted for 24 hours. Patient also reported that she had very sore gums and swelling inside of mouth. Patient reported that she was not sure if these evets were due to the vaccination.  On 13 Mar 2021, after the 2nd dose patient had begun to bleed heavily again. Patient also reported that after the first and second dose immediately afterwards there was a feeling of pins and needles in their face. This tingling sensation began on the left side of face down to the bottom of the chin with the most sensitivity on the nose and lips. This tingling sensation was far more pronounced after the second dose than the feeling of the first dose. Patient reported that the heavy bleeding and feeling pins and needles in face were present on 15 March 2021. Treatment activities for event was not provided.  The patient received both scheduled doses of mRNA-1273; therefore, action taken with the drug in response to the events is not applicable. SYMPTOM_TEXT: right leg paresthesia;   This is a report from an interventional study managed and reported by Pfizer on the sponsors behalf.   A 53-year-old female subject received the first dose of blinded vaccine therapy (BNT162;PLACEBO) on 14Aug2020 at 11:33 and the second dose on 04Sep2020 at 13:13, both via intramuscular (IM) in the left deltoid as single doses for immunization. The subject's medical history includes ongoing chronic migraines (from 2008); neck pain since 2008 with temporary relief from chiropractic manipulation; osteopenia; vitamin D deficiency (2013 to 2014) controlled with Vit D supplements until now; Vit B12 deficiency. In 2014, the subject was diagnosed with occipital neuralgia, right greater than left. She got a steroid injection and did a one-month oral steroid taper, both without relief. She declined to try gabapentin, pregabalin (LYRICA) or other neuropathic pain medications. In addition, the  chronic migraines occur 1-2 times per month requiring multiple therapeutic interventions (including B2/Mg, doxepin, zolmitriptan (ZOMIG) as needed (PRN)) and had an episode of intractable chronic migraines without aura and status migrainosus treated with botulinum toxin type A (BOTOX) in 2016. She had experienced relief with botulinum toxin type A and zolmitriptan. Per neurology visit on 01Mar2016, the subject did not feel a typical aura for the migraines, she may have some scalp tenderness or neuralgia-like feeling. She had never had a complicated migraine. Subject's family medical history relevant to adverse event was none. The subject had no concomitant vaccines or prior vaccines (within 4 weeks). Concomitant medication included zolmitriptan for migraines from 2008, vitamin D from 2013 as supplement, both ongoing. On 20Oct2020, the subject started experiencing right leg paresthesia, which required a visit to the physician's office and was considered as an important medical event. On 28Oct2020  the subject underwent a nasal/sinus surgery after which she was given codeine phosphate/paracetamol for three days. On 02Nov2020, she had lower back pain and bilateral lower extremities pain including a shooting "patchy" pain, worse on the right side. Her legs and parietal scalp were sensitive to touch with an associated burning pain. She also reported tenderness in bilateral inguinal area. Symptoms had a gradual onset approximately 3 weeks before. Subject had a magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of her back which appeared "ok" but she had not seen her primary care physician (PCP) or a neurologist. She denied a history of neurologic or lower back problems. Investigator had a follow-up on 10Nov2020. The paresthesia and skin sensitivity on head had improved but not resolved. Subject still required use of analgesic daily. At its worst, her pain was 6-7/10 in severity. When symptoms started, pain severity was 8-9/10 for a couple of weeks. Without use of analgesic, she had significantly decreased level of activity. But the pain did not prevent activity. With analgesics, she was able to function adequately despite persistence of a mild constant pain of lower back and legs which rates as 1-2/10 in severity. She had required use of some form of analgesic since pain started on approximately 20Oct2020. She had used paracetamol (TYLENOL), ibuprofen (ADVIL), codeine phosphate/paracetamol (TYLENOL#3), and most recently celecoxib (CELEBREX). She said the pain started on approximately 20Oct2020 but then said it started closer to 5 weeks after vaccination 2. She had not noticed any exacerbating factors. Subject denied any recent injury, travel, infection, or change in diet. She went for a walk on 10Nov2020 and walked approximately one mile without a problem. She stopped walking by choice not due to pain. Initially, adverse event was not reported since there was no official diagnosis and symptoms were believed to have occurred approximately six weeks after second vaccination. Despite still not having an official diagnosis, investigator had opted to report this as an important medical event since symptoms had persisted and the subject believed they started closer to five weeks after vaccination which was close to the four week post-vaccination observation period. Medical records from the neurologist were obtained. Per the note from 06Nov2020, MRI of cervical spine done several years before showed mild degenerative changes and spondylosis. MRI of lumbar spine recently done by subject showed: "degenerative discopathy, small left central disc protrusion at T5-T6 with minimal indentation thecal sac; No spinal cord compression, spinal canal stenosis or neural foramina narrowing; Multilevel hypertrophic changes of the facets within the lumbar spine with no neural foramina stenosis; Incidental finding multilevel small hemangiomas in cervical and thoracic vertebral bodies." Neurologic exam on 06Nov2020 was normal Including gait and tandem walk. Tenderness was noted in lower extremities musculature bilaterally throughout and large mobile inguinal lymph nodes palpable bilaterally. Lab ordered by neurologist were normal including Vit B12 635 (200-960PG/ML), Folate 19.6 (equal and more than 6.0UG/L), Vit D 25-Hydroxy 33 (30-100NG/ML), Total creatine phosphokinase (CK) 45 (28-176U/L), erythrocyte sedimentation rate (ESR) 15 (0-20MM/HR), C-Reactive Protein 0.3 (less than 0.5MG/DL), serum aldolase 3.9 (1.5-7.2U/L), thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH) 1.130 (0.400-4.100UIU/ML), FREE T4 1.42 (0.80-1.90 NG/DL), lyme antibody 0.25 (Negative less than 0.9), antinuclear antibody (ANA) negative; serum protein electrophoresis normal, no monoclonal protein seen. Neurologist impression included possible post-viral syndrome or an autoimmune process. There was no mention of concern for myelitis or plan for further work-up. Neurologist's recommendation was to continue celecoxib, PRN and follow-up with primary care physician if labs were unrevealing. Plan to have subject return to clinic to obtain more in-depth history and possibly some labs as well as request reports of MRIs. On 01Mar2021, the subject was seen for visit4, it was confirmed that the event was ongoing but continuing to improve. The action taken for blinded vaccine therapy in response to the event was not applicable. The outcome of the event was recovering.  The investigator considered there was a reasonable possibility that the event "right leg paresthesia" was related to blinded vaccine therapy (temporal relationship only, possible due to no other obvious potential etiologies), but unrelated to concomitant drugs or clinical trial procedure.  On 18Nov2020, the blinded code was broken due to serious, related, unexpected event.  Follow-up (10Dec2020): This is a follow-up report based on the receipt of the publication: No new information provided.  Follow-up (23Mar2021): New reported information included: clinical course (on visit4, confirmed that the event was ongoing but continuing to improve).; Sender's Comments: The event Paresthesia Lower Limb is unlisted in the Single Reference Safety Document (SRSD) of the Investigational Product blinded therapy vaccine (BNT162;PLACEBO).   There is not a reasonable possibility for the event paresthesia lower limb to be related with the blinded therapy vaccine (BNT162; PLACEBO). As an individual case report, there is not enough evidence to establish a causal relationship with the study vaccine apart from a chronological association at this time of the report. Based on the information currently available, it is more likely that the event is associated with the subject's underlying known neurological conditions.  The impacts of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product and on the conduct of the study is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committee and Investigators, as appropriate.

Heart started racing about an hour after vaccine.  this stopped after about 10 minutes.  At about 7 hours later, I became VERY lethargic, had to sit and rest.  During the rest I noticed my legs and arms started feeling extremely HEAVY, like they were being filled up with sand or cement.  They stayed so heavy that I had to lift my legs off the chair to get up and walk and then they were heavy to move.  I developed a headache as well. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Upon administering the dose, the hub became loosened from the syringe barrel and more than half the dose was lost. Vaccine ran down patient's arm and clothing. It was determined by the pharmacist and physician and nursing student that most of the dose was lost and the vaccine had to be re-administered. "Interim recommendations for COVID-19 vaccine administration errors and deviations" were followed for the second administration as such: Since "less than half of the dose was administered... administer the authorized dose immediately (no minimum interval) in the opposite arm." Thus. the second dose (0.5 mL) was given in the opposite arm (right arm). Patient did well and no other problems were noted. Patient was observed for 15 minutes and did fine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I woke up this morning and my arm near the injection site felt a bit sore again. When I looked in the mirror I have a large red round blotch on my arm. It's a bit bigger than a silver dollar. It is not perfectly round, but very close. It is not uniform in color but the round spot has a pink base color and red blotchy dots over it, but if you squint it is all one color so pretty close to being uniform. The blotch is warm to the touch and slightly itchy.  I have pretty sensitive skin so I was searching my bed for for any time of irritant but found nothing. I thought that it might be a spider bite, (I had one years ago that left a big round purple and yellow circle on my lower leg) but after some thought I realized that it is the injection site and found a few reports on the internet of something similar happening that people are calling "COVID arm." I'm not particularly concerned about it and am looking forward to my second shot. I do get hives now and again so I'm used to weird skin things!

SYMPTOM_TEXT: She got the vaccine, she went home, had no reaction.  The next day she woke up and her arms was sore, and swollen (huge).  Later on she started to have fever, cough, and then headache.  She then went to bed and slept 7-8 hours, all day long.  The swelling stayed for almost a week in her arm.  Then approximately 4-5 days later on 3/21/21 the right side of her face, the lower part of her ear to the lower part of her face started swelling, and her lip was numb.  Fearing she had Bell's palsy which she had about 10 years ago she went to see her doctor and the doctor said that it was a reaction from the vaccine.  The right side of her face and the swelling is almost gone, but her face is still feeling numb.   Her doctor did not give her anything, and since her swelling was almost gone and was improving he didn't want to give her anything for it.  He told her to watch it and if it worsens to get back to him, and to report to VAERS.
OTHER_MEDS: Advair, Albuterol HFA, Vitamin D3, Hair/skin/nails, calcium, Biotin, glucosamine chondroitin.

Shortly after vaccine administration, the pt  honked her car horn for help and was noted to be minimally responsive. Initial BP was noted to be 60/palp. She was promptly given a dose of epi (epipen) at appx. 0830. She did not improve immediately and required a second dose of epi.  Prior to transport by EMS, she improved slightly and denied any respiratory symptoms or skin involvement. She complained of feeling weak and tired only. SP02 was 89% and HR was in the 70s and regular. 02 was administered by EMS and she was given a dose of Benadryl, 25mg as well.  While EMS was still on scene with the pt, BP improved to 130 systolic and she was noted to be significantly improved.  She had a significant period of hypotension for appx. 20 minutes however (prior to improvement).  Unclear if she had a prolonged vasovagal response  or possibly anaphylaxis. She did not have clear mucosal, respiratory or GI involvement to suggest a definite diagnosis of anaphylaxis.  She was transported to local ER by EMS in improved condition.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Anaphylaxis  40 y.o. female with multiple environmental allergies, migraines, asthma, mild OSA, and anxiety presents to the emergency department from the vaccine clinic with syncope and allergic reaction.She says shortly after getting her COVID-19 vaccine, she felt lightheaded, had near syncope.   Per bystanders at the clinic, she had a brief episode of unresponsiveness and then spontaneously returned.  She was conversant with multiple members of the code and rapid response team at the bedside. Did initially have some labored breathing but significantly improved.  She had no vomiting but had mild nausea also significant improvement. In the field, IV was established and 125 mg of Solu-Medrol was administered.  She was also given 1 IM dose of epinephrine.  Her symptoms resolved she is at her baseline.  Medically stable for discharge.  Discharge home with short course of steroid, H2 blocker and Benadryl as needed.  Advised patient to follow-up with PCP post discharge.  Resume other home medicationS as listed.   Of note, the patient had a similar reaction with influenza vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: mild case of pneumonia; no appetite; body temperature was 4-5F above baseline; lost 10 pounds in 10 days; xray were similar to someone to had covid; Vomiting; Forgetfulness; uncoherent and unresponsive episode; body tremors; weakness; A spontaneous report  was received from a consumer concerning a 71-year-old male patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced memory impairment, pneumonia, asthenia, decreased appetite, body temperature increased, incoherent, vomiting tremors and weight decreased.   The patient's medical history included leukemia/AML since an unknown date in SEP-2017 and Stem cell transplant since an unknown date in JAN-2018.  No relevant concomitant medications were reported.   On 18-JAN-2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: 028L20A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On the same day, the patient experienced the events weakness, no energy, no appetite, body temperature were 4-5F above baseline. On 21-JAN-2021, the patient started experiencing body tremors and incontrollable shaking, both are worse at night. On 24-JAN-2021, he had an episode being uncoherent and unresponsive. On 25-JAN-2021, his resting heart rate was increased at 93BPM and his respiratory rate was also increased at 21 RPM. On 26-JAN-2021, he started vomiting and was forgetful. On an unknown date during a follow-up visit with PCP he was prescribed with antibiotics due to a mild case of pneumonia and suspected COVID-19.   Laboratory details included a negative COVID test performed on 22JAN2021 and some blood tests showing elevated WBC on 26JAN2021. He also had done a neuroscan and chest X-rays with unknown results.    Treatment information included antibiotics for the indication pneumonia.   Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.   At the time of this report, the outcome of the events , memory impairment, pneumonia, asthenia, decreased appetite, body temperature increased, incoherent, vomiting tremors and weight decreased was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Very limited information regarding these events has been provided at this time.  Patient's advanced age along with underlying conditions may have been contributory for the occurrence of the events. Further information has been requested.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got my shot, sat down, and was reading through the information that the clinic provided me. A few minutes after, I noticed my right arm was getting warm, but I thought I was being paranoid (placebo effect). I began to feel nauseated. About another 5 minutes after feeling warm and nauseous, my ears began to ring and my vision went white. I was cold but sweating. I have passed out a handful of times before for various reasons, so I knew what was happening. I tried to signal to a volunteer from my seat that I needed help, but I ended up laying on the ground by my chair before someone came over. Once I laid down, the attention of the volunteers and nurses was on me. Three came over to assist me. They held my legs up,  kept a hand on my wrist for a pulse, and fetched water. I talked myself through the dizziness and ringing in my ears. They put a cold rag on my forehead and had smelling salts on hand. Once I began to feel better, they helped me slowly sit up, and eventually helped me stand up and get into a chair. They kept a close eye on me for the next 30 minutes to make sure I didn?t have any other reactions.
OTHER_MEDS: 36mcg of Linzess 10mcg of Vitamin D3 Blisovi (active pill)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Previous to  Pfizer vaccines I had chronic tinnitus with mild symptoms. I'm a retired dentist. I wasn't aware of any changes in my tinnitus after the 1st vaccine. But after the 2nd vaccine I noticed a definite profound increase in my tinnitus. It is now on the verge of being debilitating in nature. It is now  pulsating and much louder, very difficult to ignore even during day time activities. Before my tinnitus was bilaterally equal, now I would say my right ear is louder than my left. But both are louder than before. Today marks about 50 days since 2nd vaccine, and I think its actually getting progressively worse! Hopefully this is not permanent.
HISTORY: Chronic mild tinnitus from years as a practicing dentist.

Initial (starting next day) - I began feeling achy, which went away after about one day. For several days I was more tired than usual and "passing out" at night earlier than I normally go to bed.  Concerning event - beginning the evening of 19 FEB 21, I began feeling tired and achy and a fever set in. From 20-27 FEB I regularly had a fever of 102-104 degrees Fahrenheit. I went to the hospital on 21 FEB after over 24 hours with a fever and a heart rate of about 115 bpm with concern of afib. During this period (20-27 FEB) I believe my heart rate did not drop below 90 bpm and was regularly in the range of 110-115 bpm. While sleeping my heart rate was commonly in the high 90s. I did not experience afib. I lost approximately 15 lbs during that week and was unable to eat. Since then I have not been able to eat a full meal based on my eating habits prior to being vaccinated. I have continued to lose weight slowly (1-2 lbs per week), but my weight will fluctuate back up by 1-2 lbs as my bowel movements are infrequent. I am currently only eating about once per day with limited snacking. I use Ensure and my vitamins to avoid concerns of malnutrition.

Client reported before vaccination a history of syncopal episodes s/p vaccine administration due to a needle phobia. Client received vaccine and had a syncopal episode while in the chair. Client slumped into a person sitting next to him. Client roused after approximately 1 minute of unconsciousness, and was initially difficult to arouse. Client was moved to a cot via wheelchair and placed in reverse trendelenberg position. Initial vitals 75/43 pulse 40, sinus bradycardia rhythm, skin was pale and diaphoretic. Client had a follow up blood pressure 5 minutes after the syncopal episode of 76/44, pulse 50. Client was offered transport versus watchful waiting by EMS staff, and opted for watchful waiting. Client had gradual return to full mentation, and skin turned to pink, warm and dry. Follow up vitals 116/82, pulse 68, spO2 100% on RA. Client continued to improve and remained in observation area for 30 minutes, and was given a ride home by his wife. Client refused transport by EMS and evaluation in the emergency department.
HISTORY: History of syncopal episodes related to needle phobia

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient described having lightheadedness, the began to experience dyspnea saying her breathing felt strange.  This began approximately 5 minutes after her dose was administered.  We had her sit down in our injection room and began to monitor her symptoms.    I immediately got out our protocol for Treatment of an Allergic Reaction as part of our vaccination program protocol.   the patient remained conscious and responsive throughout the encounter.  A pulse oximeter was placed on her left pointer finger.  Her heart rate fluctuated in the 110s to 130s during the encounter.  Her pulse ox remained 97% throughout the encounter.  Patient reported having a history of hypertension treated with lisinopril.  We placed a blood pressure monitor on her left wrist to take her blood pressure.  Her initial blood pressure was 164/105, which she reported was "just a little bit over normal" for her.  After taking the initial blood pressure, she described that her symptoms were beginning to subside a bit.  We discussed the signs/symptoms that we would be looking for in an anaphylaxis type reaction, some of which were present (i.e. tachycardia, dyspnea) and some of which were not (i.e. hives, swelling of the face/lips, throat, etc.).  We then began to take her blood pressure again.  The second blood pressure measurement was 156/104.  Shortly after taking the second blood pressure, she described having feelings of dyspnea again.  At that time, I notified another staff member to contact EMS/call 911 and let them know we potentially had an allergic reaction to the second dose of Moderna COVID-19 vaccine.  When the symptoms came back for the second time, I got out the Epipen Two Pack in the case that we would need to administer a dose.  We continued to monitor her symptoms and kept her responsive over the next few minutes, until the first set of EMS arrived from the local fire department.  The EMS staff began taking her vitals and took over care of that patient at that point.  Patient was still responsive and describing only dyspnea and having clinical symptoms of tachycardia and hypertension.  Patient got nauseated around 10 minutes after the first set of EMS arrived, and experienced a bit of vomiting.  About 10-15 minutes after the first set of EMS arrived and took over care of the patient, the ambulance and second set of EMS arrived and took over care.  They began monitoring the patients symptoms and placed an IV line.  The patient was then transported to the local Emergency Department.  At around 5PM, the patient called the pharmacy to report that the physicians at the emergency department had ruled that she had experienced an allergic, non-anaphylactic reaction to the dose of Moderna COVID-19 vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: dermatitis; eczema; postherpetic neuralgia; herpes zoster; Information has been received from a lawyer and a consumer regarding a case in litigation referring to a patient (pt) of unknown age or gender. The pt's concurrent conditions, medical history and concomitant medications were not reported. On an unspecified date, the pt was inoculated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (dosage regimen, route of administration, anatomical location, lot number and expiration date were not provided) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). After being vaccinated, the pt suffered dermatitis, eczema, herpes zoster and postherpetic neuralgia. As a result of these symptoms, the pt was seen and treated by medical providers and was still under their care. As a direct and proximate result of the pt's use of the defective zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt's symptoms resulted in physical limitations, not present prior to using the company's product. The pt also experiences mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of the conditions. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of the company's wrongful conduct, the pt suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of company's conduct, the pt suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the claimed events was not recovered, and causal relationship was reported as related to zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX).  The reporter considered dermatitis, eczema, herpes zoster and postherpetic neuralgia to be disabling events.
